<doc>
  <member name="ID3D12Heap.GetDesc">
    <summary>
      <para>Gets the heap description.</para>
    </summary>
    <returns>
      <para>Type: <b><see cref="D3D12_HEAP_DESC" /></b></para>
      <para>Returns the <see cref="D3D12_HEAP_DESC" /> structure that describes the heap.</para>
    </returns>
    <seealso cref="ID3D12Heap" />
  </member>
  <member name="ID3D12Heap">
    <summary>
      <para>A heap  is an abstraction of contiguous memory allocation, used to manage physical memory. This heap can be used with <see cref="ID3D12Resource" /> objects to support placed resources or reserved resources.</para>
    </summary>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d12/direct3d-12-interfaces">Core Interfaces</seealso>
    <seealso cref="ID3D12Pageable" />
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d12/memory-management">Memory Management in Direct3D 12</seealso>
  </member>
</doc>